channel.title: First Time modeling- God spear. Tell me what you think
channel.description: Hey guys, I'm kinda new to the whole modeling thing. This is my first, so please offer some constructive suggestions and tell me what you think, or what could improve! [IMG]http://i54.tinypic.com/kci4aw.png[/img] [IMG]http://i51.tinypic.com/315g86v.png[/img] [IMG]http://i52.tinypic.com/2r5cc5x.png[/img] [IMG]http://i53.tinypic.com/2h5scg6.png[/img]

item.title: First Time modeling- God spear. Tell me what you think
item.dc:creator: @R4z0rb14d3 R4z0rb14d3
item.description:
@R4z0rb14d3 wrote:

mmk thanks for you opinion. about the lack of design, I see what you mean, but I also must respectfully disagree. The original design was for minimalism, but the wireframe fails ;3. The reason the polygon is high is because I accidentally got the pole when I was smoothing the twirl’s mesh.
As I have said 8 times, this is a high poly version,
I have a low poly version.
I have no idea how to make twirls without running up the polys.

item.title: First Time modeling- God spear. Tell me what you think
item.dc:creator: @the_wanderer The Wanderer
item.description:
@the_wanderer wrote:

[quote=“R4z0rb14d3, post:15, topic:368552”]lol. Yeah, it started out with simplicity in mind, but I put too much effort into making it look better. Answers to all the questions above:

  1. I have the full version of the latest meta
  2. yea, poly overkill. I have a low poly version of it for future server use.
  3. I forgot the handle. I’ll add when I find a server that actually wants it -.-
  4. It does seem like a special, but it isn’t. I’m working on an array simulation script to animate the particles in a random “buzzing” motion. I just hope most servers can support animation like that.[/quote]
    Hm. Just use RsPoser to animate it. Then call on that animation when wearing that sword. An unaltered client can’t usually load a animation greater than 2^16 bytes long.

item.title: First Time modeling- God spear. Tell me what you think
item.dc:creator: @R4z0rb14d3 R4z0rb14d3
item.description:
@R4z0rb14d3 wrote:

lol. Yeah, it started out with simplicity in mind, but I put too much effort into making it look better. Answers to all the questions above:

  1. I have the full version of the latest meta
  2. yea, poly overkill. I have a low poly version of it for future server use.
  3. I forgot the handle. I’ll add when I find a server that actually wants it -.-
  4. It does seem like a special, but it isn’t. I’m working on an array simulation script to animate the particles in a random “buzzing” motion. I just hope most servers can support animation like that.
